# DS-0002: "Last USER command in Dockerfile should not be 'root'"
#
# Intentional. The container entrypoint must run as root so that the host PEM
# can be owned by UID 0 (mode 600) and therefore unreadable by the runner
# user (UID 1001). entrypoint.sh reads the PEM, mints all GitHub App tokens
# in root-process memory, and then drops privileges via gosu before exec'ing
# config.sh and run.sh — workflow jobs never run as root.
#
# See: docs/SECURITY-REVIEW-2026-04-20.md finding H-1 ("Remediation (corrected —
# verified feasible)").
DS-0002
